At the census of 1880 there were in Switzerland 211,035 foreigners (112,311 males
                    and 98,724 females), or one foreigner to every 13 or 14 of the population. The
                    origin of this alien element was very various :—from Alsace-Lorraine, 2607
                    males, 2732 females; Germany, 43,923, 45,991; Austria-Hungary, 8389, 4929;
                    Italy, 27,821, 13,709; Spain and Portugal, 175, 93; France, 26,264, 27,389;
                    Holland and Belgium, 445, 493; Great Britain, 1027, 1785; Russia, 599, 685;
                    Servia, Roumania, and Greece, 119, 35; Denmark, Norway, and Sweden, 194, 188;
                    America, 563, 548.
